### Reproduction

Steps to reproduce:
1. Add `@angular/cdk` to the project
2. Import `OverlayModule`
3. Inject Overlay to some component through DI
4. Create a portal to render the template (you should define it in the HTML + query it thourgh ViewChild)
5. Create an overlay
6. Attach portal to the overlay

I created two examples on stackblits with ivy and without ivy. Looks like stackblitz can not work in ivy mode. You can clone the example and execute `npm i` && `ng serve --open`. You will be able to reproduce the problem (links are below).

Looks like the problem is strongly connected with `NgIfDirective` since if you remove it everything works fine.

#### Examples (stackblitz, github repos)

##### With Ivy:
Stackblitz example does not work in Ivy mode despite of enableIvy flags in the angularCompilerOptions section of the `tsconfig` file. Looks like Ivy is not working in stackblitz. You can check tsconfig, it is enabled. Tell me please if it can be easily fixed.

Stackblitz example: https://stackblitz.com/github/sharikovvladislav/angular-cdk-overlay-woot-with-ivy
Repo: https://github.com/sharikovvladislav/angular-cdk-overlay-woot-with-ivy
##### Without Ivy: 
This example is working. I just wanted to present what means "expected behavior".
Stackblitz example: 
https://stackblitz.com/github/sharikovvladislav/angular-cdk-overlay-ok-without-ivy
Github Repo: https://github.com/sharikovvladislav/angular-cdk-overlay-ok-without-ivy

The code of the component looks like:

```
  constructor(private overlay: Overlay, private _viewContainerRef: ViewContainerRef) {
  }

  toggle() {
    if (!this.overlayReference) {
      const overlay = this.overlay.create();
      const optionsPortal = new TemplatePortal(this.listOptionsTemplate, this._viewContainerRef);
      // there is the problem
      overlay.attach(optionsPortal);
      this.overlayReference = overlay;
    } else {
      this.overlayReference.dispose();
      this.overlayReference = null;
    }
  }
```
 
 
#### Expected Behavior

I expect, that created template will be inserted to the overlay element (body > .cdk-overlay-container > .cdk-overlay X)


#### Actual Behavior

Created element is placed somewhere near the HTML-tags of AppComponent.

This is how the DOM looks like before creating the overlay:
